item.title: [WFLY-682] Custom JSF deployment does not work altogether with CDI

item.summary: Custom JSF deployment does not work altogether with CDI

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: For this to work, somebody would need to do an AS7 implementation of the SPI for MyFaces and then bundle it with the WAR. At some point I may get around to it as part of the effort to have MyFaces fully integrated with AS7.
Unassigning from myself since this is open to community.

If I understand the pull request right this is fixed for wildfly and it is possible to use Weld with 2 JSF implementations now?
Are there plans to make this working on EAP6.1?
Yes, it is fixed in WildFly, but there are no plans to backport.

customfieldvalues.customfieldvalue:
1) Download the zip provided in http://community.jboss.org/message/622383 and extract it
2) add a beans.xml inside the WEB-INF folder
3) Deploy it to a JBoss AS 7.0.1 instance (7.0.0 won´t work because of AS7-1541)
